It’s Here FINALLY! 

After 5 months of drafts & moving from TX —— CA…my latest single “Overflow” has dropped globally on every major music outlet!

Hear it on:
- Spotify
- AppleMusic 
- Pandora
- iHeartRadio
- SiriusXM
- YouTube Music
- Shazam
- Napster
- DEEZER
- SoundCloud
- Beatport
And other MAJOR labels! 

“Overflow” is a statement of freedom. A statement of love. A statement of rebellion. An overflow of emotions that makes us who we are. A celebration of youth. Make it what you want.

Inspiration for this piece started in Galveston, TX while I was stationed there with my last USCG unit & ended while strolling on the beaches of Bodega Bay, CA while attending “A” School ⚓️

Can’t wait to drop this along with my upcoming EP on tour next year! Cheers everyone!

Today marks the 5th Anniversary of my mom’s passing & the toughest period of my life. It’s been a journey. 

This time of the year is always an emotional one for myself & the fam. 2018 I really got tested & almost threw it in.

5 years ago in the span of 6 months; Lost my dog “Kiwi” of 13 years, lost my mother to colon cancer & had a childhood friend take his own life. Rock bottom. 

I was a mess. Full out manic depression, suicide attempt & overdose; and medicated & counseled professionally. Almost gone at 24 years.

Had it not been for pops, the family & close friends, my therapist & church group…don’t know where I’d be today. I can never repay them. 

But I got up, refusing to disappoint my Mother; knowing it’s not what she wanted. It’s amazing what can happen to you at your lowest point.

It was at this time especially that my drive for producing took off. I just needed to vent. Started writing poetry, journaling & producing music non-stop; both as a DJ & singer-songwriter. 

It’s helped me connect with others in a way I wasn’t able to before & helped me connect with my audience more. What you create isn’t just about you. It’s a bigger picture. 

Looking back, I realize how far I’ve come, the things I’ve achieved & people I’ve met: At college, in the military & the music / entertainment industry. 

To anyone who’s hurting tonight, know that you’re never alone. Never quit. Never give up. Reach out & never forget your worth. 5 years strong. Not stopping anytime soon. 

#cykloidmusic #anniversary #5years #recovery #staystrong

What a time it’s been since “Overflow” was released back in January. First single to hit over 10,000+ streams on Spotify. Still at a loss of words…

“Somewhere” is a project where I did a lot of exploring. Both in the physical & the soul; while experimenting with Melodic Dub-Step, a genre I’m not used to being a Future & Tropical house artist.

2023 being the 5th anniversary of having lost Mom to cancer & her b-day coming up the 25 of July, I wanted to make something that celebrated her but also celebrated life. A journey that never stops surprising.

Curiosity. Adventure. Innocence. Energy. Passion. Love. Risk.

No matter where we are, where we go, who we meet or who we end up with…we’re always…“SOMEWHERE”.

Releasing globally AUG. 23 💿📲

RECAP PHOTO-DUMP 1/4 - Cykloid Music “Summer Endz” Tour

This past weekend was absolutely INSANE. Truly. I’m speechless…From opening up for @morganpage with @sonder.events915 & @churchbarept to throwing sets down at @jaxrooftoplounge & @blitzsportsgrill 🏴‍☠️🔥

In what was one of the CRAZIEST weekends of my music career thus far; I take time to reflect on how far I’ve come in 10 years. 

From a scrawny little kid with oversized glasses dreaming big in small New Mexico desert town…to touring across the country (and soon the world) with the Cykloid Music crew, it’s been a journey & I get emotional.

I’ve had so many people in my life help me along the way. My Dad, my family, music partners, sponsors, fellow brothers & sisters in arms in the military & some of my best friends @jose_uri3l & @ryanmakoo & of course the fans.

And with that the Cykloid Music “Summer Endz” tour comes to an end. Wonder what’s next? 😎 

Can’t wait for events in the Fall, Puerto Rico, 
Spring Break Mexico ‘24 & Germany next year! 🇵🇷🇩🇪🇲🇽

SALUD & CHEERS EVERYONE! ❤️

Photo Cred: @joshuabeingmusic / @maggieaadams / @cykloidmusic

2023 Patrol Recap VIDEO ⚓️:

So happy to be back on land & home in Charleston, SC! Few more weeks & I’ll be back at my real “HOME” in New Mexico! 🌵🏜️ Can’t wait to see Dad, family, friends & fans!

Commissioning a new vessel has been crazy. Long nights. Lack of sleep. Added with a bunch of non-stop laughter, shenanigans & memories!

Had a time celebrating Thanksgiving and my Birthday with the crew & also earning bragging rights by becoming the first DJ in U.S. Coast Guard history to perform a gig underway at sea! 

YES SIR!!! Add another milestone to the scrapbook! Remember the name! 😎🔥

Cheers to the crew of USCGC CALHOUN! Love you all & looking forward to many more crazy times together! Wonder what April has in store!
